        <num>CC 1476</num>
        <heading>1476.  Minors; incapacity to make donations, exceptions</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1476.  Minors; incapacity to make donations, exceptions
A minor under the age of sixteen years does not have capacity to make a donation either inter vivos or mortis causa, except in favor of his spouse or children.
A minor who has attained the age of sixteen years has capacity to make a donation, but only mortis causa.  He may make a donation inter vivos in favor of his spouse or children.</p>
        </content>
